where is the least likely place

00:29:05.620 --> 00:29:10.630
anybody would care about this
positive, virtuous, saccharin

00:29:10.630 --> 00:29:15.780
sweet, soupy, syrupy,
touchy feely, naive--

00:29:15.780 --> 00:29:19.630
eww-- pollyannish stuff?

00:29:19.630 --> 00:29:22.060
Likely, Wall Street.

00:29:22.060 --> 00:29:24.876
I mean, if I got $100 million
invested in that portfolio,

00:29:24.876 --> 00:29:26.500
and I'm in a hedge
fund, I want to know

00:29:26.500 --> 00:29:28.666
if it's going up or down,
because I've got one goal.

00:29:28.666 --> 00:29:29.950
Show me the money.

00:29:29.950 --> 00:29:31.367
That's all I care about.

00:29:31.367 --> 00:29:32.950
I don't care if you
treat people well.

00:29:32.950 --> 00:29:34.030
I don't care if you downsize.

00:29:34.030 --> 00:29:34.670
I don't care if you--

00:29:34.670 --> 00:29:35.830
I don't care what you do.

00:29:35.830 --> 00:29:37.820
I want a return.

00:29:37.820 --> 00:29:39.910
So we picked 40 firms.

00:29:39.910 --> 00:29:42.114
When they implemented
positive practices,

00:29:42.114 --> 00:29:43.280
some did better than others.

00:29:43.280 --> 00:29:44.371
So we measured change.

00:29:44.371 --> 00:29:46.370
Or in other words, how--
are you getting better?

00:29:46.370 --> 00:29:47.460
Are you getting worse?

00:29:47.460 --> 00:29:48.730
Are you staying the same?

00:29:48.730 --> 00:29:52.900
When organizations improved,
got more and more virtuous,

00:29:52.900 --> 00:29:57.580
essentially, we could
account for almost 50%--

00:29:57.580 --> 00:30:03.040
0.45-- 45% of their
financial performance.

00:30:03.040 --> 00:30:05.350
Now, I don't know anything
that predicts Wall Street

00:30:05.350 --> 00:30:08.259
